## Most Useful Storage Commands

```bash
lsblk

lsblk -f

sudo mkfs -t ext4 /dev/nvme3n1

sudo mkdir /mnt/ebs-storage

sudo mount /dev/nvme3n1 /mnt/ebs-storage

sudo umount /mnt/ebs-storage

df -h

df -Th

sudo blkid

sudo file -s /dev/nvme3n1

mount

mount | grep nvme

touch test.txt
```

## Key Takeaway

Before a new EBS volume can be used:

1. Attach the volume.
2. Verify with `lsblk`.
3. Create a filesystem using `mkfs`.
4. Create a mount point using `mkdir`.
5. Mount the volume using `mount`.
6. Verify using `df -h` and `lsblk`.
7. Test by creating files on the mounted storage.
